{
  "texts": [
    "After we looked at the results involving the no incentive condition, we then looked at the comparisons between GPT and all other incentives conditions.",
    "We did not find evidence in our sample that the reappraisal quality gap between GPT and humans decreased across the conditions, for any of the reappraisal quality outcomes.",
    "We therefore cannot conclude that increasing monetary incentives was associated with increasing reappraisal quality (see Supplemental Materials for full breakdown).",
    "We further quantified the observed null effect with a Bayesian approach.",
    "We fit four Bayesian generalized multivariate linear multilevel model using the brms (Bürkner, 2017) package in R, with default priors and a gaussian distribution."
  ]
}